🍑 Less than 24 hrs and nurses couldn’t believe I just had a baby…👆🏻So, how was I able to start the healing, recovery and baby weight loss/tummy pouch process immediately after delivery?

🍑 To start and pregnant or not, BUILD your HEALTH so your body can handle anything you throw at it including pregnancy🤰🏼, delivery and postpartum🤱🏼. 

🍑 MOVE daily, walk everywhere and add regular strength training. Even 15 min of resistance training can do wonders. Focus on quality (rather than quantity) nutrient dense whole foods preferably organic grass fed meat, limiting processed products. I never weigh myself. So when your body endures a stressful event like pregnancy and delivery, it’s stacked, armed and ready to fight for you. 👊🏻

🍑 Don’t try to be a particular number as that will NEVER satisfy or define you. If you actively practice patience and dedication, the RESULTS of your consistent work will be soon become EVIDENT. 

🍑 It took your body 9 full months to get here so give yourself 9 months to return to normal. Be gentle and compassionate with yourself and body (ALWAYS). Don’t compare yourself to ANYONE. Everyone’s body reacts differently to pregnancy, postpartum and nursing!! Some people can train really hard and it doesn’t affect their supply. Some see dips with not as extreme workouts. Some get leaner faster, some take longer.  I keep the blinders on and do ME and I encourage you to do the same :) 

Also: vaginal birth and on demand breastfeeding 🤱🏼 stimulate the uterus to start contracting back.

🤱🏼 It is reasonable to want to get back to your pre-pregnancy weight. However, the most important thing in the postpartum period is to make sure that the mother and baby are well-nourished. If breastfeeding is the goal, excessive calorie reduction can reduce both the quantity and quality of the milk🍼 and is not recommended.

🤱🏼 How Many Calories Does Breastfeeding Burn?

It comes down to your body and the amount you breastfeed. Exclusive breastfeeding typically burns about 500-700 calories per day, less if partially breastfeeding.

🤱🏼So... Does Breastfeeding Help You Lose Weight?

Possibly. But putting too much emphasis towards this is not recommended. Breastfeeding shouldn't be seen as a weight loss mechanism. It has negligible effect on body fat and total body weight for most well-nourished women. It may help to get you to your pre-pregnancy weight slightly quicker—but again, it depends on the woman's lifestyle.💕

1 week postpartum 💗🙏🏻🤱🏼

Contrary to popular belief, one of the best things you can do to drop the baby weight fast is by allowing time for your body to heal, feel safe, calm and parasympathetic mode in order to shed the extra weight.

You just gave birth to another human being!! That’s a big deal. 

Ever hear the saying that it takes a village to raise a child?

Well, that same village would have helped a new mom heal after childbirth. Whether it be by making her meals, helping with the newborn (or her other children), and most importantly by letting her rest as much as possible!

If a family member or friend offers you help, do yourself a favor and accept it. The more you can rest and heal, the sooner you can get moving again!

3 ways a savoury breakfast 🥚🍳🫑changed my life.

1. Sweet breakfasts 🧇🧃🍌release dopamine in the brain 🧠, therefore giving us pleasure, but they give our body less availability energy 🔋 than a savoury breakfast. Going savoury trades short term pleasure for long term energy. 

2. If you start your day with a sweet breakfast 🥞, you kick off a glucose rollercoaster 🎢 and non-stop cravings 🍩🍫for the day. A savoury breakfast prevents that from happening.

3. A savoury breakfast 🍳 around protein 🥚🥓🥩🧀 keeps our hunger hormones at bay and is the pillar for steady glucose and feeling great 🤸🏼‍♂️😊🧘🏼‍♀️.

Do you eat breakfast? What is your go to? If you are in a weight loss plateau, your (type of body) may do better with a breakfast (to lower cortisol) despite the fasting trends you may have explored.

😊 If your goal is to support hormone, thyroid, and adrenal health, you need to be proactive about managing stress and cortisol. 

🍳 Eating breakfast 🥚🥑🥐 actually helps your body bring down cortisol levels, which are the highest early in the morning.
